Voutas said his cousin also told him he went to the cockpit to check what waswrong and saw the pilot "all blackened."
Greek government spokesman Theodoros Roussopoulos said that when the F-16 pilotsflew by the Helios Airways plane a second time, they saw two people apparentlytrying to take control of the Boeing 737.
After the plane lost contactwith air traffic controllers "for more than an hour," saidIoannis Pantazaratos, head of the air traffic control tower atEleftherios Venizelos International Airport, "we had no idea who wasflying the plane."
